request.description:
**Note:**Â this endpoint is available in Alfresco 5.2 and newer versions.

Updates the nodeÂ **nodeId**. For example, you can rename a file or folder:

``` json
{
  "name":"My new name"
}

```

You can also set or update one or more properties:

``` json
{
  "properties":
  {
    "cm:title":"Folder title"
  }
}

```

You can update multi-value properties of a node which supports properties of type multiple.

``` json
{
 "name":"My Other Folder",
 "nodeType":"custom:destination",
 "properties":
 {
   "cm:title":"Folder title",
   "cm:description":"This is an important folder",
   "custom:locations": [
                        "location NewX",
                        "location NewY"
                       ]
 }
}

```

**Note:**Â setting properties of type d:content and d:category are not supported.

**Note:**Â if you want to add or remove aspects, then you must useÂ **GET /nodes/{nodeId}**Â first to get the complete set ofÂ *aspectNames*.

You can add (or remove)Â *locallySet*Â permissions, if any, in addition to any inherited permissions.  
You can also optionally disable (or re-enable) inherited permissions viaÂ *isInheritanceEnabled*Â flag:

``` json
{
  "permissions":
    {
      "isInheritanceEnabled": false,
      "locallySet":
        [
          {"authorityId": "GROUP_special", "name": "Read", "accessStatus":"DENIED"},
          {"authorityId": "testuser", "name": "Contributor", "accessStatus":"ALLOWED"}
        ]
    }
}

```

**Note:**Â if you want to add or remove locally set permissions then you must useÂ **GET /nodes/{nodeId}**Â first to get the complete set ofÂ *locallySet*Â permissions.

**Note:**Â Currently there is no optimistic locking for updates, so they are applied in "last one wins" order.

